<HL>
   British Unit Labor Costs Rise
</HL>
<DATE>
06/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   LONDON -- Wages and salaries per unit of output in the
manufacturing industry in April rose a seasonally adjusted
0.7% from March and increased 7.6% from a year earlier,
Britain's Central Statistical Office said.
   The index, which is based on the year 1985 equalling 100,
was 121.3 in April and 120.4 in March; year-earlier figures
have been revised and aren't comparable.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the three months through April, the index of unit
labor costs rose 8.1% to 120.8 from a year earlier, compared
with an 8.1% annual rise to 120 in the three months through
March.
</TEXT>
