06/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12
</SO>
<CO>
   FCBN
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   LAGUNA NIGUEL, Calif. -- Furon Co. said it plans to redeem
all of its outstanding $23.4 million face amount of 8%
convertible subordinated debentures due 2011.
   The maker of polymer products said it will pay $1,048.88
on July 19 for each $1,000 face amount of debentures. The
debentures may be converted prior to the close of business
July 18 into shares of Furon common at a rate of 74.42 shares
for each $1,000 face amount of debentures.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Any debenture holder who converted the debentures would
receive shares and cash for fractions of shares with a total
value of $1,302.35 based on yesterday's closing price of
$17.50. The actual value will vary with the stock price at
the time of conversion.
   A regular interest payment of $40 for each $1,000 face
amount of debentures will be paid July 16 to bonds of record
June 30. Any debentures converted before July 16 won't be
entitled to any interest.
