<HL>
   International Brief -- Lloyd's of London:
   Exchange and Sun Alliance
   Set European Insurance Plan
</HL>
<DATE>
06/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16
</SO>
<CO>
   U.SUN U.SDW U.WIL
</CO>
<IN>
INSURANCE (INS)
</IN>
<LP>
   Lloyd's of London, the insurance exchange, and Sun
Alliance PLC joined to market big-risk insurance in Europe,
the two sides said.
   The joint venture between Sun Alliance, Britain's biggest
general insurance company, and Lloyd's is aimed at drawing
European-based business to London in the wake of the European
Community's forthcoming market unification.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Called Eurosure, the insurance will be marketed through
Lloyd's four biggest brokers, CT Bowring &amp; Co., Alexander
Howden Ltd. and the insurance-broking units of Sedgwick Group
PLC and Willis Faber PLC.
   Sun Alliance and 35 Lloyd's underwriting syndicates will
give the brokers a ready facility to arrange policies on
large risks that they might otherwise find difficult to
handle, a Lloyd's spokesman said.
   The areas of risk to be covered are property, business
interruption, public and product liability and marine cargo
cover.
</TEXT>
