<HL>
   Business Brief -- Flextronics Inc.:
   Disk-Drive Maker Expects
   To Post 4th-Quarter Loss
</HL>
<DATE>
06/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FLEX
</CO>
<LP>
   Flextronics Inc. said it expects to report a fiscal
fourth-quarter loss of $22 million on sales of about $41
million.
   Results for the quarter ended March 31 include costs
associated with the Fremont, Calif., company's recently
completed sale of a 55% stake in its Asian operations to an
investment group.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the year-earlier quarter, the disk-drive maker reported
a loss of $8.6 million on sales of $50.1 million.
   Flextronics said the asset sale will result in
"significant net profit" for the current quarter after
accounting for a onetime after-tax gain of about $13 million.
It didn't estimate the profit.
   ---
   Corrections &amp; Amplifications
                                                                                                       

   FLEXTRONICS Inc., an electronics manufacturer, said a
fiscal fourth-quarter loss that it expects to report stemmed
from costs associated with the sale or closure of certain
U.S. operations. In Tuesday's edition, the cause of the loss
was misstated.
   (WSJ June 21, 1990)
</TEXT>
